  <!-- Commonly-used symbols, terms, and abbreviations specific to
  this document.

  To avoid clashes with any built-in entities, we use a capital Q as a
  prefix for all of our names.  The only exceptions are for the qm
  components.

  We use capital letters in the prefix, followed by lowercase for that
  name itself, or if the name is in uppercase, we separate it from the
  prefix with an underscore.  The prefixes are:

  Q	A "simple" use of the abbreviation.  This may be hyperlinked to
	a defining term.

  QF    A "first use" of a term.  This should define a id attribute for
	references to this term.  This should be used when a new term
	is introduced, or the first time a an external system or
	command is mentioned.

  QR	A "raw" version of a term, with no hyperlinking at all.  This
	should have the appropriate text attributes.  The other forms
	are generally defined using the QR form.

  QFL	A "lesser first use" of a term.  This should be formatted like
	a first use, but hyperlinked to the QF version.

  -->

